<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-21T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-21T10:00:00-05:00" n="526" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d526">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2353/5: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-21T15:00:00+00:00">January
                                    21, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>116. My 94, January 18. Military Attaché has discussed this matter with
                            higher military authorities. They have agreed to submit to Salazar<note n="24" xml:id="d526fn24">Antonio de Oliveira Salazar, President of
                                the Portuguese Council of Ministers and Minister for Foreign
                                Affairs.</note> question of juridical status of planes grounded in
                            these circumstances. They have also undertaken to consider a business
                            offer for the purchase of the planes.</p>
                        <p>War Department has been informed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>